# MV3 Architecture and Messaging
- `src/background/service-worker.js` is the MV3 service worker entrypoint and must keep async message handling (`return true` + `sendResponse`). (Do not name it `index.js`: `@crxjs/vite-plugin` chunks by basename and would merge it with `src/content/index.js`.)
- Route all runtime messages through `src/background/message-router.js` and keep the response envelope stable: `{ ok: true, data }` / `{ ok: false, error }`.
- Message names must come from `src/messaging/message-types.js`; do not introduce ad-hoc string literals.
- UI callers (content/popup/options/viewer) should use `sendMessage()` from `src/messaging/send-message.js` instead of direct `chrome.runtime.sendMessage`.
- Background/service modules may use direct `chrome.*` APIs when they are the ownership layer (for example `chrome.storage` in `settings.service.js`).
- Viewer mount flow should remain traceable: `src/content/index.js` -> `src/content/bootstrap.js` -> `src/viewer/app.js`.
- Use `logger` (`src/shared/helpers/logger.js`) for logs so prefixes and log levels stay consistent.
